Top AnswerI recommend paying cash for the cabs! They tend to add a surcharge if you're paying with credit card. Also, there's this amazing low-key place that sells amazing pan roast (lobster is my favorite!) called Oyster Bar. It's 24/7 but only allows a bar seating for up to 13 people at a time (so it's a pretty long wait). I think the best, money-saving trip to have is to grab a fat tuesday and walk down the strip at night! Catch the water show at the Bellagio, play some penny slots at Caesar's Palace, and grab a slice of "Secret Pizza" at the Cosmopolitan. Hope you two have fun! :)





